      p Nolphons are negatively charged particles. Antinolphons, their positively-charged counterpart, are also commonly known as hoverons (due to initial misclassification).
      p Under ordinary conditions, a nolphon-antinolphon pair annihilation will result in the release of photons. However, under very high-energy conditions, nolphon-antinolphon pair annihilation can result in a complicated chain of events that happen in a single tick, creating a nolpherino-antinolpherino pair (sometimes known as a nolpherino-hoverino pair).



