    .col-md-6
      p A modern-day Nolphin engine contains a micro black hole, which is saturated with what are generally known as "bees". Contained in such an environment, bees vibrate at a frequently that asymptotically approaches 60Hz (conventionally truncated to 60.0000001Hz).
      p It is a widely accepted but unproven theory that large numbers of nolpherinos and antinolpherinos form the entity known as a bee. This theory is supported by the force-carrying-boson nature of nolpherinos and existing observational findings, but as no method yet exists for observing units of time smaller than a tick, there is no direct proof. Scientists debate if sub-tick measurements are even theoretically possible, some saying "the discrete nature of the unit of time we call a tick is a fixed mechanic of the universe".
